It’s that time… reflecting back on the very very high highs and very low lows this year… if you’ve ever felt dumb I assure you I’ve felt dumb and dumber this year learning little things about my business that might seem like common sense to some but didn’t to me! 🤓❄️🤣✨

✨Owning your own business or multiple businesses is not for the faint of heart… 

❄️personally  I’ve had the BEST year of my life getting engaged to my love, moving into our home and acquiring the new home of GLAMP montana!  but I’ve also had my WORST year financially in 5 years…. 

This year I lost 2 of my biggest clients and had to recreate six figures worth of income with no warning- it’s been an insane year for all of us but I know times like these make us think even more creatively as entrepreneurs and that is the gift that keeps on giving ✨

💕With all of the stress and setbacks it’s ok - this year I LEARNED- (mostly against my will)but I learned a ton and will put everything nto practice for the best year yet! It’s yet to come and I can feel it falling into place! 

Going into 2023 with a strong plan, strong team, and strong boundaries which for a people pleaser was my hardest one yet… 

✨🙏Thank you for the opportunity to grow with me and to get to do what I love more days than not! I am living my dream and despite any setbacks I’m grateful for that! 

Excited about working with some incredible brands social strategy and content creation over on @lovemondaymedia excited to continue creating magic right here in my photography business and super excited for #glampmontana to grow! Cheers to 2023 and all the lessons this past year has taught us all!

I can promise you after 15 years in the industry… most ideas have been done before even if you’re not aware of that and guess what- that’s ok!!!! 

✨ YOUR unique vision can only be shot by YOU! That’s the beauty of photography! Every person even shooting the exact same shot in the same place at the same time is going to see it differently, edit it differently, present it differently- that’s the most fascinating part of this entire thing we devote our lives to! 

💖 Be respectful - If you’re directly inspired by someone reach out to them or mention it in your caption ! If your shooting with someone or on a styled shoot, workshop, or mentorship program remember that it’s the person directing intellectual property and just ask how they would like it shared or presented- everyone is different don’t assume every photographers answer will be the same! Always ask- it’s not hard! 

💘Don’t get discouraged - with SO MUCH content being created alllll the time it can feel so overwhelming and draining to come@up with something new but inspiration is ok- your version of it is going to be different by default! Be inspired but just remember to acknowledge and most of all to just have fun and create! At the end of the day it’s just photos! Don’t get caught up in industry pressure - you became a photographer for the joy of creating! Don’t lose that! #photographeradvice #contentcreatoradvice #creatives #creativecommunity #create #creativephotography #valentinesphotoshoot

Typical #personalbranding shots you can expect from me look like this! 

✨My editing style is light, airy, and commercial! 

✨We will use props and we will have fun. I will make you laugh and it’s the moments inbetween that you’re going to use. 

✨I’m super bossy so don’t worry I’ll tell you what to do the entire time and show you how you’re looking… 

✨I’m also the hair police because it can be the best photo in the world but if you don’t like your hair you don’t use it (and that just hurts my heart)

Luck number SEVEN 🫶🏻✨🤩
Do you know what the Rule of 7 is? 

If you’re in marketing, you’ve probably heard the term before. 

The Marketing Rule of 7 states that a consumer needs to “hear” an advertiser’s message at least 7 times before they’ll take action to buy that product or service. 

✨ Yup, that’s right! At least 7 times. This rule applies to social media and the digital age of marketing. 

Every brand, content creator, and influencer has an opportunity to reach their consumers at least 7x a day. Think about that for a sec. 

Just on Instagram you have access to:

→ Reels
→ In-feed posts
→ IG Lives
→ Guides
→ IG stories
and so much more…

So with that all being said, STOP feeling off about saying the “same thing” or creating content around the same message because your potential clients & customers need to hear it multiple times before they take action. 

We would argue that Instagram Stories are one of the top ways to engage with your audience and release touchpoint throughout the day easiest. 

Don’t forget, some people don’t even scroll on their feed vertically- they do it horizontally with IG stories. 

They’re quick & easy. Don’t assume your audience sees every in-feed post.

They probably don’t. However, by diversifying your content on platforms you have more of a chance to be seen. Diversify and reuse content but don’t stop that messaging!

BOUNDARIES have been REALLY challenging for me… in my personal life and ESPECIALLY in my business! 

✨ I think it’s actually a positive thing because I LOVE what I do so much and that passion mixed with a very compulsive personality makes for a dangerous mix sometimes… 

These are the things I’m working on and the intentions I’m setting for the new season ahead- hello September, hello new season first time being a wife and putting my family’s happiness first and foremost. 

✨ I’ve worked really hard to be at the place in my career where I can say no, I can work with jobs and individuals that align with MY values and take on projects that spark creativity and joy! 

I’m not saying it’s easy and I fail at this ALL the time but I just feel like if I put it out there and into the universe and share it maybe I can remind myself to realign when things get hectic and I fall into unhealthy habits …

🫶🏻Creating an intentional work schedule and sticking to it
Saying NO to things that aren’t on your priority list

Not taking on more client work when you’re at your max

Not constantly giving free advice or showing up anytime you are asked

Phone “down time” at night and in the morning 

Setting expectations with clients and employees upfront with clear deadlines and communication

A lot of you guys have been asking me how I got started…. 

 I picked up a camera when I was 14. It was film. I learned in a dark room… I have been shooting 35 mm, holga , fish eye sardine cams, restoring vintage cameras and shooting on film before it was “cool” before instagram was invented. Yes, I’m that old. Or rather I was that young… 

✨I have only really been naturally good at two things in this life: using a camera and being extra so here we are many years later doing the same thing… 

Black and white was my thing and it still is in many ways … it’s always come natural to me- seeing light in this very strange way. I have been told I have an extra cone in my eye so I’m super light sensitive but I’m also pretty blind at night- it’s weird but I have this biological advantage - I was created to do this. 

I’m proud of my black and white images I feel like I could have taken them today… she loves an up angle 😂😂 these were shot circa 2005-2011 …. Buttttt my early color work- weddings/commercial / all the things— it’s a different story! It’s a whole different ball game when models, brands all of that is involved! It’s hard girl I see you! 

My early commercial and branding work- WILDLY awful and embarrassing but I want to show it to you here- working on a reel to show the evolution because you will scream. 

I’m not an overnight success…. I’m self taught (my degrees are in marketing and business) I attribute my schooling to amazing mentors and trial and error- just PLAYING! 

My biggest advice to photographers starting out (at any age) is to go get experience- I encourage you to just go shoot ! Find a friend, find an object and you might just find yourself along the way. 

That’s what I’m doing for the rest of my day I’m just going to go play around and I will learn something I personally guarantee it! #blackandwhitephotography #filmphotography #photographerlife #photographycoach #photographymentor #womeninbusiness #smallbusinessowner

Am I not the luckiest person in the world to get to play dress up and make people realize they are stunning and can live their wildest dreams?

Growing up I wanted to be a reconstructive plastic surgeon (well first I wanted to be Ariel from the little mermaid for like way longer than was appropriate - were talking my teacher had to call my mom in to chat because I kept signing my papers “Ariel”) yet I digress… 

My brothers are brilliant but I do not have the skill set to change the world via surgery or a mermaid tail so I settled for the strange and magical gift of showing people how they actually look on the inside… 

I’m really just so grateful to have this weird super power or X-ray vision where I can see what your insides are made of and bring it to the outside so you can see it too… I feel like sometimes clients think I’m being fake but I’m not I genuinely just see beauty in all things and I want you to see it too.. maybe it’s my competitiveness or just wanting to prove I’m right but I genuinely want you to see yourself how I see you. 

We all focus on our own flaws- I’m super guilty of this. But if we can step back for a moment and see the beauty in each other- that’s where the golden moments are born. 

Teaching and uncovering this skill set (you probably already have it you just might not realize it yet) has been so rewarding. I want you to have this feeling. Maybe you’re a creator, a photographer, a videographer, a stylist, an mua, a model I don’t know who you are but you have something worthwhile to bring to the table and when we all get together to create something other worldly happens… that’s what these workshops/ portfolio builders do for me- they bring all of these elements together to offer the opportunity for creativity, community, collaboration and Just freaking joy.

My number one career advice is super simple and when I heard this audio I had to post it just to remind you young ones out there or maybe you’re not a young one but you’re finally ready to get serious about your career.

POV: my clients after their personal branding session… 

Yes it’s a feel good service- you’re going to feel amazing and see yourself how I (and probably the rest of the world see you!) as your badass stunning self- so confidence boost is a CHECK … 

As great as a new profile picture can be there is much more to your personal branding shoot and why we invest so much time money and energy into creating personal brands- we want to tell a story, express ourselves, and tell the world what we do and who we are… this concept is abstract which is what makes it such a fun challenge for me… 

I speak with clients all the time and the story is usually the same… they say: “ I just don’t know how to “be seen” and build a strong digital image of my business. Isn’t it enough to just throw up a website with some details about my services?” 

Yes- correct you do need a website but most people’s first point of contact with your brand is actually on social media- it’s your very few seconds to make an impression (usually visually above all else)… 

So you do your branding shoot, you make some posts and you put that website up, and you know what happened? 
Yep, not much!

This was the problem: I’m sure your website is very pretty, and it was packed with info about your work, but the problem is there is no where you’re expressing your true self, your ideas, your personality, the exact pain points you and/or your business solve- all of this messaging is a lot to expect a few photos and a website to accomplish… 

You NEED to express why you or what you offer matters to a potential client. Telling this story and getting this messaging across takes a multifaceted visual strategy through photo, video, graphics, stories ect- it’s so much more than some glam shots of you in a studio sis… thats just the tip of the iceberg…

If you’re overwhelmed on where to start with your branding, your storytelling, and your digital assets it’s ok- it’s normal. But I’m here to help- to brainstorm to spam you with Inspo to hype girl you to help you choose your outfits to make your mood board - let’s talk. You got this. #branding #brandingphotographer
